- NodeJs is an open source, cross-platform JavaScript runtime environment and library for running web application outside the client's browser

- It is used for creating server-side application.

- Perfect for data intensive, realtime web applications as Node.js never waits for an API to return data

- Better synchronization of code between server and client due to same code base.

- Easy for web developers to start using Node.js in their projects as it is a Javascript library.
